Bespalova*, M.A. Bovina, M.B. Sergeeva, V.D. Oppengeim, V.G. Zaikin Academy of Sciences, Leninsky Prosp., 29, 117912, Moscow, GSP V-71, Russian Federation Abstract Homogeneous catalysts WCIb 1,1,3,3-tetramethyl-1,3-disilacyclobutane and WClb-lihydrodiphenylsilane allow cross-metathesis of cycloolefins (cyclopentene, cyclooctene) and norbornene with ethyl-4-pentenoate, allyl cyanide, all yltrimethylsilane. Self-metathesis of functionalized olefins with two unconjugated carbon-carbon bonds takes place with high yields and selectivity. Key words: homogeneous catalysts; metathesis; olefins; silicon-containing catalysts; tungsten 1. Introduction It has been shown in our previous studies [ 1 ] that the catalyst WC16 1,1,3,3-tetramethyl1,3-disilacyclobutane (DSCB) is active in metathesis of functionalized olefins with a short chain length. In the presence of this catalyst self-metathesis of allyl cyanide and ethyl-4pentenoate and their cross-metathesis with olefins and alkenylsilanes can occur with relatively high yields and selectivity. Therefore this catalyst was applied for other reactions especially for those which can produce new valuable products. Silicon-containing catalysts have low toxity in comparison with tin- or lead-containing homogeneous and heterogeneous catalysts which are usually applied for the metathesis of functionalized olefins [ 2] . Organosilicon co-catalysts are tolerant to moisture and oxygen from the air, so they are convenient in operation. In the present work we demonstrate the possibility of applying homogeneous silicon- *Corresponding author; fax ( +7-095)2302224. 0304-5102/94/$07.00 1994 Elsevier Science B.V. Bespalova et al. /Journal of Molecular Catalysis 90 (7994) 27-27 containing catalysts based on WC16 in cross-metathesis of cycloolefins with functionalized olefins. A lot of studies have been devoted to examine the influence of small quantities of acyclic olefins or functionalized olefins on the molecular weight, yield and cis-content of the polymer produced from cycloolefins. About 150 unsaturated compounds containing functional groups have been screened for their effect [ 3 ] . It has been shown that acrylonitrile was an inhibitor [ 4] , while alkenylsilanes could act as catalysts for ROMP [ 5 ] . So it seems to be very interesting to study cross-metathesis reactions between such substrates when the molar ratio cycloolefin/functionalized olefins > 1. 2. Experimental 2.1. Reagents 2.1.1. Catalysts WC16 was purified by vacuum sublimation and kept under argon. DSCB was preparated by reaction between chloromethyldimethylchlorosilane and Mg [6] and distilled from sodium before use. 2.1.2. Solvents Benzene was refluxed for 12 h over sodium, then distilled and stored under dry argon over sodium wire. 2.1.3. Substrates Bicyclo[2.2.1 ] hept-2-en was purified by sublimation and distillation from sodium wire. Cyclopentene and cyclooctene were distilled from sodium and stored over 4A molecular sieves. Allyl cyanide (Fluka) was dried with PZOS and distilled before use. Allyltrimethylsilane was obtained from allyl bromide, chloromethyltrimethylsilane and Mg [ 7 ] , distilled from sodium and stored over 4A molecular sieves. Ethyl-4-pentenoate, ethyl (2-allyl) -pentenoate and methyl (2-allyl) -pentenoate were prepared from allyl bromide and ethyl acetoacetate [ 8 ] and distilled before use. All substrates were kept under argon. 2.2. Analysis Reaction products were identified by GLC on a Chrom-5, using a glass column containing 8% of SE-30 with DMCS on Carbowax W (80/100 mesh, programmed for 10 C min-' from 60 to 180 C, He as carrier gas). Mass spectra were measured on a Kratos MS-80 spectrometer at ionizing voltage of 70 eV, IR spectra-UR-20 instrument. 'H NMR spectra were recorded in CDC13 with TMS as the internal standard on a Bruker MSL 300 spectrometer. N.B. Bespalova et al. /Journal of Molecular Catalysis 90 (1994) 21-27 23 2.3. Procedure The reactions were carried out in liquid phase in sealed tubes under vacuum (1 X 10-3 mmHg). The calculated amount of the unsaturated substrates was introduced into the tube. Next, benzene solutions of DSCB and WCI6 were added. All the additions were made at room temperature under argon. The reaction mixture was frozen by liquid nitrogen, argon was evacuated by vacuum, and the tube was sealed. Then the mixture was heated to 60-80 C for 10 h. After cooling, the products were fractionated by distillation. 2.3.1. Characterization of the main products CHZ=CH(CHZ)3CH=CHCHZCN (Ila). B.p. 96-98 C (15 mmHg). Result and discussion The reactions of cycloolefins (cyclooctene, cyclopentene) with allyl cyanide were investigated. The homogeneous system WCI6- DSCB acts as catalyst for the reactions: - 0- ).. An increase in the amount of allyl cyanide brought about an increase of the yields of (Ila, IIb). The best results were obtained when the molar ratio of (I)/cycloolefins was 2/1. Formation of these products could result from secondary metathesis reactions of (11) with allyl cyanide or with other products of self- and cross-metathesis reactions. Besides 13-15% of oligomers, a small amount (5-7%) of dinitrile (IV) was also found. Both of these products originate from self-metathesis of substrates. Cometathesis of cyclooctene with allyltrimethylsilane produces silicon-containing unconjugated diene with high yield: + CH2 cat CH2 + 6 -CH2 + 0 b CHCHZSi(CH3)3 CHCH~Si(CH3)3 V +(CH~3SiCH2CH=CHCHZSi(CH3)3 + ofigomers Self-metathesis of both substrates were side reactions. Reaction of (V) resulted in the formation of 1,4-bis(trimethylsilyl)-2-butene with 18-20% yield. Polymer produced from cyclooctene was not detected. Only oligomers (n=2-4) were obtained (15-18%). Small amounts of other products (secondary cross-metathesis, isomerization etc.) were identified on the basis of the GC-MS analysis. The selectivity of the main cross-metathesis reaction reached 70-80%. It is interesting to note the co-metathesis reactions take place in the presence of WC16 DSCB catalyst and in absence of DSCB cocatalyst, because allylsilane can act as cocatalyst. Previously, this was shown for ROMP [5] and for self-metathesis of allylsilanes upon WOC14 [10] and WC16 [11]. Table 2 shows the decrease in metathesis conversion when the reaction occurs without DSCB cocatalyst. From these studies it can be concluded that cycloolefins undergo cross-metathesis reactions with different functionalized olefins, which resulted in production of functionalized dienes if homogeneous silicon-containing co-catalyst is present. Reactions of the cross-metathesis of norbornene with functionalized olefins have received little attention. As a rule, small quantities of linear olefin were used to reduce the polymer chain length, when ROMP of cycloolefins was carried out [ 12,13 ] . Unsaturated symmetrical esters undergo cross-metathesis with norbornene [ 14] . Bespalova et al. /Journal of Molecular Catalysis 90 (1994) 21-27 We studied the reaction between norbornene and ethyl-4-pentenoate at equal molar ratios of substrates with formation of cross-metathesis products. Two silicon-containing catalysts: WC16-DSCB and WChPhZSiHz were used. The latter one was applied for self-metathesis of functionalized olefins [ 15 ] . + Iii 1~ CHCH2CH2COOC21~ VII VIII CI-Lz=CH~ CH=CHCH2CI-IZCOOCJ~ IX + CHz=CH- ^ -CH=CHz + X (trace) HSCZOOC(CHZ)zCH=CH- ^ -CH=CH(CHZ)2COOC2H5 XI (trace) The formation of unsymmetrically substituted product is favoured in co-metathesis reactions. These results agree with those obtained for co-metathesis reactions of 5-acetoxynorbornene and 5-cyanonorbomene with 1-pentene [ 16] . The side reactions are self-metathesis of both substrates and secondary reactions produced (X) and (XI) as minor products. Table 3 shows the relatively high selectivity of this reaction, so it can be applied for synthesis of unsaturated esters with cyclopentane fragments. It may be used for synthesis of various natural compounds and their synthetic analogues. NB. Bespalova et al. /Journal of Molecular Catalysis 90 (1994) 27-27 27 Surprisingly, this reaction occurs with high selectivity and yield. The formation of cyclic product is nearly quantitative. This result could be explained by the difficulties occurring when five-membered substituted cyclic olefins were polymerized. Success in producing these reactions depends on the nature of substituents and their position in the ring [ 3 ] . It is well known that only a few catalysts are active for the metathesis of functionalized substrates. Silicon-containing systems WCI,- DSCB' (or PhzSiHz) show high catalytic properties for these reactions. It can be explained by the formation of organotungsten precursor of active species resulting from the reaction between WC16 and DSCB. This compound has a bulky alkylsily1radical which can inhibit the coordination of substrate at the W-atom [ 1 ] . The metal-silylene intermediate is suggested to initiate the metathesis reaction with WCIb-PhZSiHZ catalyst [ 15 ] . 4. Conclusion Homogeneous silicon-containing catalysts permit high yields in cross-metathesis reactions between cyclic (or bicyclic) and functionalized olefins and self-metathesis reaction of unconjugated dienic esters. These catalysts can be applied for synthesis of various organic products which contain cyclopentane or cyclopentene fragments. References [ 1 ] N.B. Bespalova, M.A. Bovina, J. Mol.
